    "domain" : "5",
    "comment" : {
      "en" : "Relates a Construal to its constituent sub-situations, each representing an individual premise as perceived by the cognizer. The relation is recursive — a sub-Situation may itself have parts that ground it further, mirroring the CRMinf premise chain (J1 usedAsPremise). Each sub-Situation may optionally satisfy a dul:Description (e.g. a Framester frame), representing the inference logic (CRMinf J3 applies) through which that premise is interpreted. The conclusion drawn from the full Construal is always an opino:Opinion (dul:Description), connected via opino:grounds."
    },
    "attributes" : [ "object" ],
    "id" : "4"
  }, {
