      "en" : "Relates a Construal to any entity — object, agent, event, or abstract concept — that the cognizer perceives as participating in the construed state of affairs. Following the social psychology notion of construal (Ross 1987), the entities involved are not neutral facts but are perceived and interpreted through the cognizer's subjective lens. The Construal grounds the Opinion (subclass of Description)."
    },
