      "en" : "Relates a Construal to another Construal that it makes possible as a subsequent step in an inferential chain. A Construal enables another when it provides the evidential or logical basis from which the subsequent Construal can be constituted. For example, the Construal 'Fief is a Medieval Latin term' enables the Construal 'The Donation contains anachronistic Latin', which in turn grounds the Opinion 'The Donation is a Forgery'. Inverse counterpart of opino:presupposes in the inferential chain, though not declared as a formal OWL inverse. Subproperty of dul:hasPostcondition."
